{% comment %}
This file is "included" from each of the tag-efficient.md, tag-flexible.md
etc files to render all standards associated with the given tag.

Renders each standard as a compact list row matching the visual weight of
the other `one-*.liquid` includes on the same page (qualities, requirements,
approaches). The previous version delegated to standard-item.liquid, which
wraps each title in an <h3> — appropriate on the categorised standards
listing (where standards are the page subject) but far too heavy on tag
pages, where standards sit as one of four peer sections.

The `standard-item.liquid` partial is intentionally left untouched here so
the categorised standards listing keeps its heading-level weight.
{% endcomment %}

{%- assign tag_to_find = include.tag -%}
{%- if tag_to_find and tag_to_find != "" -%}

{% comment %}
  Standards classify by topical `categories` (security, safety, ...),
  while tags use shorter slugs (secure, safe, ...). The shared mapping
  lives in `_data/tag-aliases.yml`.
{% endcomment %}
{% assign category_to_find = site.data.tag-aliases[tag_to_find] | default: tag_to_find %}

<div class="panel standards-header" id="standards">
  <h2>Standards tagged with #{{ include.tag }}</h2>
</div>
<div id="search-results">
  {% assign filtered_standards = "" | split: "," %}
  {% for standard in site.standards %}
    {% if standard.categories contains category_to_find %}
      {% assign filtered_standards = filtered_standards | push: standard %}
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}

  {% if filtered_standards.size > 0 %}
    <ul class="posts no-bullets">
      {%- for standard in filtered_standards -%}
        <li>
          <a href="{{ standard.url | prepend: site.baseurl }}">{% include icon.html name="award" size="xs" class="bullet" style="color: var(--standard-text-color);" %} {{ standard.shortname | default: standard.title }}</a>
        </li>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </ul>
  {% else %}
    <p>No standards tagged with #{{ include.tag }} yet.</p>
  {% endif %}
</div>

{%- endif -%}
